column5: Is your workplace clean and tidy?
column9: Is furniture and equipment in good working order?
column10: Does any furniture or equipment pose a risk?
column11: Is all the equipment in good working order?
column12: Are the surfaces of furniture and equipment clean and dust free?
column13: Are the shelves and filing cabinets securely fastened to the wall and/or floor?
column14: Are the shelves and filing cabinets overloaded?
column17: Are all the office lights working?
column18: Do any of the light fixtures need new bulbs or tubes?
column19: Electrical cords, plugs and sockets are in good condition
column20: Are there any electrical outlets overloaded?
column22: Have extension cords been in use for more than 30 days to supply temporary power?
column23: Do extension cords pose a tripping hazard?
column25: Are the power bars affixed to the wall, or furniture?
column26: Is an approved portable electric heater in use?
column27: Is the heater plugged directly into a wall receptacle?
column28: Is there a minimum 3’ clearance maintained around the heater at all times?
column29: If office is accessible to public, handling valuables (i.e. cash) is done in a secure place
column30: Are staff members familiar with evacuation, lock-down, medical & security procedures?
column31: Adequate lighting in and around work areas.
column33: Does the lock on the door function properly?
column36: Are any items stored within 18" from the bottom of the sprinkler heads?
column37: Is more than 20% of wall space covered with combustibles?
column38: Have extinguishers in the area been inspected for the month?
column39: Does the first aid kid in the area have adequate supplies?
column40: Is the cabinet accessible and clean?
